<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3F6A80FCE4917D1CE0B22D" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3F6A80FCE4917D1CE0B22D" blockId="196.[790,1385,1749,2177]" lastBlockId="196.[177,1384,2183,3480]" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FC4C917D1A04BC77" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[944,1028,1828,1861]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FBE1917D1A8BBC77" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1053,1163,1828,1861]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">muricola</taxonomicName>
species group. Formerly included in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FB81910D1B2CBC5F" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1149,1324,1876,1901]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
, to which genetic data suggestit is most closely related; limits between the two species are uncertain, especially in the 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3F6A80FB35919B1B67BCD1" box="[1225,1383,1986,2019]" name="Philippines" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Philippines</collectingCountry>
where they co-occur; see also M. brown: and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FCA59E481A53B300" authorityName="Hill &amp; Francis" authorityYear="1998" box="[857,1107,2065,2098]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gomantongensis">M. gomantongensis</taxonomicName>
. Perhaps also related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FC919E611A27B36B" authorityName="Kruskop &amp; Borisenko" authorityYear="2013" box="[877,1063,2104,2137]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annatessae">M. annatessae</taxonomicName>
, although that species did not cluster with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FBC49E391A99B3B3" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[1080,1177,2144,2177]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FB369E391B69B3B3" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1226,1385,2144,2177]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
in recent studies. To date, genetic studies of this species have used only specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3F6A80FEFD9EF71F7BB3FD" box="[257,379,2222,2255]" name="Vietnam" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
; material from other regions needs testing, to provide a fuller picture of internal variation and external relationships. Race nugax is occasionally placed in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FF4F9EA71F52B22D" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[179,338,2302,2335]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
